<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8eb595d5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s280a"><num value="280a">§ 280a.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When used in this subchapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8eb595d6-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s280a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the term “Secretary” means the Secretary of State;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8eb595d7-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s280a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the term “Government agency” means any department, independent establishment, or other agency of the Government of the United States, or any corporation wholly owned by the Government of the United States; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8eb595d8-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s280a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> the term “Commission” means the South Pacific Commission.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id8eb595d9-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-01-28/ch38/s2">Jan. 28, 1948, ch. 38, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/15">62 Stat. 15</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
